
Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I go to Page 07 of Thoracic CT

When I select 'Finding' radio button
Then 'Finding' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Fracture of scapula' from the dropdown menu
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Right' radio button is enabled
And 'Left' radio button is enabled
And '14A: Process' radio button is enabled
And '14B: Body' radio button is enabled
And '14F: Glenoid fossa' radio button is enabled
And '14: Not further defined' radio button is enabled


When I select '14A: Process' radio button
Then '14A1: Coracoid process' radio button is enabled
And '14A2: Acromion' radio button is enabled
And '14A3: Spine' radio button is enabled

When I select '14B: Body' radio button
Then '14B1: Exits the body at 2 or less points' radio button is enabled
And '14B2: Exits the body at 3 or more points' radio button is enabled

When I select '14F: Glenoid fossa' radio button
Then '14F0: Extraarticular' radio button is enabled
And '14F1: Simple, articular' radio button is enabled
And '14F2: Multifragmentary, articular' radio button is enabled

When I select '14: Not further defined' radio button
Then 'Fracture older, remodeled' radio button is enabled
And 'Suspected' radio button is enabled
